WEBVTT

1
00:01:04.528 --> 00:01:07.061
Okay, let's try it again.

2
00:01:13.683 --> 00:01:16.453
We saved this one, but let's do one more.

3
00:01:22.096 --> 00:01:24.577
Just one more.

4
00:01:30.492 --> 00:01:33.092
We keep it. One more.

5
00:01:34.639 --> 00:01:36.512
We keep this one too.

6
00:01:37.418 --> 00:01:39.049
Gyu Hui.

7
00:01:39.049 --> 00:01:40.958
Gyu Hui!

8
00:01:40.958 --> 00:01:42.518
Gyu Hui!

9
00:01:43.418 --> 00:01:45.573
I can't do this.

10
00:01:45.573 --> 00:01:47.526
Because?

11
00:01:47.526 --> 00:01:49.012
Hey...

12
00:01:54.849 --> 00:01:57.539
Just today they intern Nara,

13
00:01:57.539 --> 00:02:00.729
and you had to make the song so difficult.

14
00:02:00.729 --> 00:02:04.726
Not that anyone who knows how to play this
appears out of nowhere.

15
00:02:04.726 --> 00:02:06.573
Maybe... Hee Jeong?

16
00:02:06.573 --> 00:02:07.836
Hee Jeong?

17
00:02:07.836 --> 00:02:10.036
Do you think I didn't try to call her?

18
00:02:10.036 --> 00:02:11.293
saw the sheet music

19
00:02:11.293 --> 00:02:14.116
and said it would take at least a week.

20
00:02:14.116 --> 00:02:16.013
I don't blame you,

21
00:02:16.013 --> 00:02:17.570
I'm just saying take it easy.

22
00:02:17.570 --> 00:02:20.233
Be a little more flexible.

23
00:02:20.829 --> 00:02:22.086
That?

24
00:02:22.086 --> 00:02:23.573
Yun Ju?

25
00:02:24.837 --> 00:02:26.630
I guess someone did come.

26
00:02:26.630 --> 00:02:29.695
I heard you were back in Korea.

27
00:02:29.695 --> 00:02:31.975
I didn't expect this!

28
00:03:12.248 --> 00:03:13.693
Hello, Do Hyun.

29
00:03:13.693 --> 00:03:16.086
<i>Jun Kyung, did you eat?</i>

30
00:03:16.086 --> 00:03:18.540
I was waiting to eat with you.

31
00:03:18.540 --> 00:03:19.993
Do you have a long way to go to finish?

32
00:03:19.993 --> 00:03:21.620
<i>It might take a little longer.</i>

33
00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:24.506
<i>I think I'll have lunch with Jung Hoon later.</i>

34
00:03:24.506 --> 00:03:26.140
<i>Make sure you eat,</i>

35
00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:28.300
<i>you must be hungry.</i>

36
00:03:41.216 --> 00:03:43.373
<i>Jin Ho,</i>

37
00:03:43.373 --> 00:03:46.216
<i>Have you seen Bom?</i>

38
00:03:46.216 --> 00:03:48.456
<i>I can't find it anywhere.</i>

39
00:03:51.389 --> 00:03:53.043
Ja Yeong,

40
00:03:53.572 --> 00:03:55.333
are you okay?

41
00:03:57.300 --> 00:04:00.286
I must have fallen asleep for a second.

42
00:04:01.625 --> 00:04:03.685
I dreamed about Bom.

43
00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:09.803
It felt so real that I thought it was happening.

44
00:04:11.290 --> 00:04:12.970
God.

45
00:04:13.603 --> 00:04:15.575
So it was just a dream.

46
00:04:17.109 --> 00:04:19.021
It must have scared you.

47
00:04:19.021 --> 00:04:20.763
Yes.

48
00:04:20.763 --> 00:04:22.643
I'm sorry.

49
00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:28.837
<i>You only have to have five million ready.</i>

50
00:04:29.395 --> 00:04:33.252
<i>Many teachers are looking
those optional subjects,

51
00:04:33.252 --> 00:04:35.150
<i>and the complaints are endless.</i>

52
00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:37.883
<i>As long as you have that amount ready,
You'll be fine.</i>

53
00:04:43.610 --> 00:04:44.870
Okay,

54
00:04:44.870 --> 00:04:46.582
finish and come quickly.

55
00:04:52.803 --> 00:04:54.743
The director liked it.

56
00:04:58.810 --> 00:05:00.170
Send your account details to Jung Hoon.

57
00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:02.656
Isn't that too formal?

58
00:05:07.620 --> 00:05:08.960
Thank you.

59
00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:11.620
- Enjoy your food.
- Thank you.

60
00:05:13.299 --> 00:05:16.019
I haven't eaten hagfish in years.

61
00:05:19.079 --> 00:05:22.279
Just when I played, it brought back memories.

62
00:05:22.853 --> 00:05:25.864
In first year, on Jongno Street,

63
00:05:25.864 --> 00:05:28.620
I played the song you had made on the piano.

64
00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:31.666
Do you remember when people gathered?

65
00:05:38.445 --> 00:05:42.519
Do you know how much I liked you back then?

66
00:05:46.745 --> 00:05:49.585
Do even those memories bother you?

67
00:05:51.326 --> 00:05:54.272
I also thought about the past.

68
00:05:57.166 --> 00:05:58.695
At that time...

69
00:05:59.886 --> 00:06:02.485
I also liked you a lot.

70
00:06:06.776 --> 00:06:08.109
But...

71
00:06:09.909 --> 00:06:11.822
like you said,

72
00:06:11.822 --> 00:06:13.802
They are just memories.

73
00:06:25.409 --> 00:06:28.102
I'm sorry, I should go.

74
00:06:28.596 --> 00:06:32.069
Jun Kyung is waiting.
I shouldn't stay here.

75
00:06:40.713 --> 00:06:42.615
And what about me?

76
00:06:44.599 --> 00:06:47.439
You are what I need now.

77
00:07:02.622 --> 00:07:05.372
We finished a long time ago.

78
00:07:08.659 --> 00:07:11.685
I will do the best I can as Daniel's father...

79
00:07:13.987 --> 00:07:16.480
But that's all there is between us.

80
00:07:17.489 --> 00:07:19.119
Where are you going?

81
00:07:20.292 --> 00:07:21.873
Hey!

82
00:08:06.639 --> 00:08:08.845
I know.

83
00:08:10.339 --> 00:08:13.452
I know Jun Kyung is with Do Hyun now.

84
00:08:15.606 --> 00:08:18.159
But they've only been together two years.

85
00:08:20.132 --> 00:08:22.878
We have known each other for a long time...

86
00:08:25.740 --> 00:08:27.433
and we have...

87
00:08:28.399 --> 00:08:30.265
to Daniel.

88
00:08:32.173 --> 00:08:34.986
I thought that made me stronger.

89
00:08:37.092 --> 00:08:39.638
There is no stronger or weaker.

90
00:08:47.458 --> 00:08:49.155
So,

91
00:08:49.155 --> 00:08:51.205
what are you going to do now?

92
00:08:52.150 --> 00:08:53.618
Don't know.

93
00:08:55.060 --> 00:08:56.807
What do I do now?

94
00:09:04.081 --> 00:09:07.141
<i>Joy and sadness</i>

95
00:09:07.141 --> 00:09:10.440
<i>they always seem to come out of nowhere.</i>

96
00:09:12.143 --> 00:09:16.200
<i>Especially sadness.</i>

97
00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.323
<i>There is a tribe in Africa</i>

98
00:09:22.323 --> 00:09:25.846
<i>who believes that the rain
It is a sign of God's pain.</i>

99
00:09:26.480 --> 00:09:27.857
<i>So when it rains,</i>

100
00:09:27.857 --> 00:09:30.125
<i>they stay outside the town</i>

101
00:09:30.125 --> 00:09:32.746
<i>until it stops raining...</i>

102
00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:36.364
<i>until the sun rises</i>

103
00:09:36.364 --> 00:09:38.735
<i>and the ground will dry up.</i>

104
00:09:40.044 --> 00:09:42.048
<i>In Seoul now,</i>

105
00:09:42.048 --> 00:09:44.708
<i>it rains without warning.</i>

106
00:09:46.614 --> 00:09:48.871
<i>Is it a sign of sadness</i>

107
00:09:48.871 --> 00:09:51.117
<i>what does God send us?</i>

108
00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:54.204
<i>You,</i>

109
00:09:54.204 --> 00:09:56.710
<i>did they bring umbrellas?</i>

110
00:10:01.786 --> 00:10:04.247
He also played Bom like this,

111
00:10:04.247 --> 00:10:06.860
and she stayed very still.

112
00:10:07.766 --> 00:10:11.406
I still remember how soft it was
the back of his little head.

113
00:10:13.852 --> 00:10:16.000
The good memories

114
00:10:16.487 --> 00:10:18.713
They are the ones that make it more difficult.

115
00:10:20.793 --> 00:10:22.859
If I had known it would be like this,

116
00:10:22.859 --> 00:10:25.885
I wouldn't have tried so hard.

117
00:10:30.300 --> 00:10:32.586
Erase that package from your mind,

118
00:10:32.586 --> 00:10:34.712
do you think it still exists?

119
00:10:37.230 --> 00:10:39.980
Do you remember those travelers we saw in Jeju

120
00:10:39.980 --> 00:10:41.743
when did we eat?

121
00:10:43.036 --> 00:10:44.792
Jin Ho...

122
00:10:46.696 --> 00:10:48.863
don't you hear that?

123
00:10:52.680 --> 00:10:54.333
The rain?

124
00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:25.713
Jun Kyung, where did you go?

125
00:11:25.713 --> 00:11:27.660
It's pouring.

126
00:11:27.660 --> 00:11:30.219
You should have brought an umbrella.

127
00:11:31.866 --> 00:11:34.459
The umbrellas always seem to be nearby,

128
00:11:34.979 --> 00:11:37.519
but they are never there when you need them.

129
00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:46.066
I lied to you.

130
00:11:54.660 --> 00:11:56.033
Before,

131
00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:59.086
when we talk on the phone...

132
00:12:01.473 --> 00:12:03.399
was with Yun Ju.

133
00:12:07.379 --> 00:12:10.112
I thought it would make you uncomfortable...

134
00:12:12.736 --> 00:12:14.642
so I didn't say anything.

135
00:12:17.350 --> 00:12:19.896
I thought lying would be better.

136
00:12:28.204 --> 00:12:29.504
I'm sorry.

137
00:12:32.386 --> 00:12:34.851
I went to your studio before.

138
00:12:42.710 --> 00:12:45.222
Thanks for being honest with me.

139
00:13:13.239 --> 00:13:15.553
I thought about it a lot...

140
00:13:17.313 --> 00:13:18.693
and alone

141
00:13:19.266 --> 00:13:21.646
I wish it was the right time.

142
00:13:31.023 --> 00:13:33.270
When you need me...

143
00:13:34.743 --> 00:13:36.763
and when not...

144
00:13:38.742 --> 00:13:40.229
I will always be

145
00:13:41.269 --> 00:13:43.742
at your side

146
00:13:58.241 --> 00:13:59.714
Jun Kyung...

147
00:14:01.888 --> 00:14:04.568
would you marry me?

148
00:14:36.001 --> 00:14:38.560
- Hello, dad.
- Hello.

149
00:14:38.560 --> 00:14:39.780
Are you busy?

150
00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:42.080
<i>I'm fine. What's happening?</i>

151
00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:44.433
It's nothing serious.

152
00:14:45.700 --> 00:14:47.880
It's about Ja Yeong.

153
00:14:47.880 --> 00:14:51.022
He seemed better after coming here,

154
00:14:51.022 --> 00:14:52.835
but he's not sleeping well.

155
00:14:52.835 --> 00:14:55.126
She seems more nervous lately.

156
00:14:55.126 --> 00:14:57.565
and a little sad.

157
00:14:58.159 --> 00:15:00.699
I heard there's something called
pet loss syndrome.

158
00:15:00.699 --> 00:15:03.400
Maybe that's what's happening to you.

159
00:15:03.400 --> 00:15:05.076
Pet loss syndrome?

160
00:15:05.076 --> 00:15:06.200
<i>Yes.</i>

161
00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:10.866
<i>Many people do therapy
after losing a pet.</i>

162
00:15:12.593 --> 00:15:15.592
After all, he lost his family.

163
00:15:19.550 --> 00:15:20.870
TRUE.

164
00:15:20.870 --> 00:15:23.070
Why don't you come visit her?
with Do Hyun and Jun Seo?

165
00:15:23.070 --> 00:15:24.950
I haven't seen you in a while.

166
00:15:24.950 --> 00:15:27.416
I also miss Daniel.

167
00:15:27.416 --> 00:15:29.650
We'll go, dad.

168
00:15:29.650 --> 00:15:31.390
I'm sorry I didn't call more.

169
00:15:31.390 --> 00:15:33.310
I know you're busy. Thank you.

170
00:15:33.310 --> 00:15:34.517
You are welcome.

171
00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:36.350
<i>By the way...</i>

172
00:15:37.443 --> 00:15:39.623
You're fine, right?

173
00:15:43.600 --> 00:15:45.380
I'm fine.

174
00:15:45.380 --> 00:15:47.500
<i>Okay, see you soon.</i>

175
00:15:48.060 --> 00:15:49.633
Yes.

176
00:16:00.253 --> 00:16:01.947
Ja Yeong,

177
00:16:02.752 --> 00:16:04.865
what are you looking at like that?

178
00:16:13.173 --> 00:16:15.066
The five-day market should open today.

179
00:16:15.066 --> 00:16:16.980
Do you want to go see?

180
00:16:16.980 --> 00:16:18.748
We can buy some things,

181
00:16:18.748 --> 00:16:21.414
maybe eat <i>jajangmyeon</i> for a change.

182
00:16:21.414 --> 00:16:22.991
Jin Ho.

183
00:16:22.991 --> 00:16:24.657
Yeah?

184
00:16:24.657 --> 00:16:26.584
Coming here like this,

185
00:16:27.118 --> 00:16:29.644
Don't you think it was too hasty?

186
00:16:30.684 --> 00:16:33.870
As if we were running away.

187
00:16:39.719 --> 00:16:41.843
Jin Ho!

188
00:16:41.843 --> 00:16:43.596
Hey.

189
00:16:44.513 --> 00:16:46.220
Don't you like this place?

190
00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:47.817
- That?
- Answer me.

191
00:16:47.817 --> 00:16:49.899
Don't you like this place?

192
00:16:49.899 --> 00:16:52.540
- It's not that...
- You said it yourself.

193
00:16:52.540 --> 00:16:54.244
You wanted to live in a place

194
00:16:54.244 --> 00:16:56.233
where were you first
to see the flowers open,

195
00:16:56.233 --> 00:16:59.264
to feel the sun on your face,
in stepping on fallen leaves.

196
00:16:59.264 --> 00:17:01.520
You said it.

197
00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:03.780
We weren't running away.

198
00:17:05.233 --> 00:17:08.406
I felt a little trapped.

199
00:17:09.467 --> 00:17:11.783
I didn't think it through.

200
00:17:11.783 --> 00:17:13.639
I'm sorry.

201
00:17:14.199 --> 00:17:16.772
I think I was too sensitive.

202
00:17:27.417 --> 00:17:32.123
You and Jun Kyung live together, right?

203
00:17:32.674 --> 00:17:37.230
Which basically means
who are already concubines.

204
00:17:37.230 --> 00:17:41.076
You are only one step away.

205
00:17:41.643 --> 00:17:43.310
Just one more step.

206
00:17:43.310 --> 00:17:46.130
This is hard for her now.

207
00:17:48.780 --> 00:17:50.243
Clear.

208
00:17:50.779 --> 00:17:52.540
It's just...

209
00:17:52.540 --> 00:17:54.860
my job is unstable

210
00:17:55.733 --> 00:17:57.960
- and I have a son.
<i>- It's like that.</i>

211
00:17:57.960 --> 00:18:02.925
If there is at least one percent
of doubt behind a proposal,

212
00:18:02.925 --> 00:18:04.745
It never feels good.

213
00:18:05.732 --> 00:18:07.765
It's not about her.

214
00:18:09.740 --> 00:18:12.026
Isn't it because of the boy

215
00:18:12.026 --> 00:18:14.379
And it's not because of the boy's mother?

216
00:18:15.233 --> 00:18:17.100
So what is it?

217
00:18:17.100 --> 00:18:19.260
This is not your problem.

218
00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:21.224
For Jun Kyung,

219
00:18:21.224 --> 00:18:23.899
the marriage itself... you know?

220
00:18:23.899 --> 00:18:25.040
How do I say it?

221
00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:28.520
He's already thought about it a thousand times,

222
00:18:28.520 --> 00:18:32.040
even all the wildest scenarios.

223
00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:35.800
That's what intelligent and pessimistic people do.

224
00:18:35.800 --> 00:18:37.304
The point

225
00:18:37.304 --> 00:18:41.004
It's not about you or anyone else.

226
00:18:42.863 --> 00:18:44.967
Jun Kyung has something,

227
00:18:44.967 --> 00:18:48.646
an obsession that can never fail.

228
00:18:48.646 --> 00:18:51.040
Kind of like perfectionism, basically.

229
00:18:51.619 --> 00:18:53.420
It's for me.

230
00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:58.274
Difficult to understand, isn't it?

231
00:19:00.796 --> 00:19:02.267
Yes.

232
00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:05.254
I really don't understand it

233
00:19:05.254 --> 00:19:07.554
and I don't identify myself at all.

234
00:19:09.710 --> 00:19:12.150
Do Hyun is a good guy, really.

235
00:19:13.036 --> 00:19:15.200
showed me

236
00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:19.066
that happiness comes from being with someone.

237
00:19:20.436 --> 00:19:22.456
What is the problem?

238
00:19:24.357 --> 00:19:26.376
I don't feel safe.

239
00:19:31.410 --> 00:19:34.447
Dealing with what I already know is overwhelming.

240
00:19:34.447 --> 00:19:37.379
If something unexpected happens between us,

241
00:19:37.379 --> 00:19:40.550
some disaster that we cannot control...

242
00:19:42.636 --> 00:19:46.322
I know I would want to run away.

243
00:19:51.206 --> 00:19:53.059
Yes.

244
00:19:53.059 --> 00:19:56.565
It must have been difficult for your dad, right?

245
00:19:57.566 --> 00:19:59.440
No.

246
00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.013
I think my mom had it worse.

247
00:20:03.846 --> 00:20:07.152
He couldn't hold on, he couldn't let go.

248
00:20:08.559 --> 00:20:11.552
I think he suffered more.

249
00:20:38.845 --> 00:20:40.019
How serious is it?

250
00:20:40.019 --> 00:20:41.912
A total collapse.

251
00:20:42.390 --> 00:20:43.883
And Jun Kyung?

252
00:20:43.883 --> 00:20:45.170
It's sincere.

253
00:20:45.170 --> 00:20:47.423
Enough to give up a diamond.

254
00:20:48.243 --> 00:20:51.170
I never saw Do Hyun so serious.

255
00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:53.010
You won't think

256
00:20:53.010 --> 00:20:55.243
They are going to separate, right?

257
00:20:55.989 --> 00:20:58.394
A couple that went out enough,
at the right age,

258
00:20:58.394 --> 00:21:00.860
but can't take the next step?

259
00:21:00.860 --> 00:21:02.205
Yes, that happens.

260
00:21:02.205 --> 00:21:04.710
Even though they are clearly in love?

261
00:21:04.710 --> 00:21:07.385
Love is supposed to end in marriage.

262
00:21:07.385 --> 00:21:09.910
That's how social animals are.

263
00:21:09.910 --> 00:21:11.890
Love and marriage go together.

264
00:21:11.890 --> 00:21:13.210
That's legit.

265
00:21:13.210 --> 00:21:15.534
If someone is not the one
to be with you,

266
00:21:15.534 --> 00:21:18.674
instinct drives you to find
to someone who is.

267
00:21:19.930 --> 00:21:21.876
Does this really hurt you?

268
00:21:23.876 --> 00:21:25.583
No.

269
00:21:29.639 --> 00:21:31.111
Maybe a little.

270
00:21:31.833 --> 00:21:33.372
Just a little.

271
00:21:35.819 --> 00:21:37.512
I'm sorry.

272
00:21:50.700 --> 00:21:52.500
Believe...

273
00:21:54.040 --> 00:21:58.026
that your time will come.

274
00:22:03.162 --> 00:22:05.099
I will wait for it

275
00:22:05.099 --> 00:22:07.165
with an open heart.

276
00:22:26.616 --> 00:22:28.070
Gracias

277
00:22:28.070 --> 00:22:29.862
to understand.

278
00:22:44.006 --> 00:22:46.752
This is completely rotten.

279
00:22:52.966 --> 00:22:55.332
Wow, you scared me.

280
00:22:59.160 --> 00:23:01.080
Can you do this?

281
00:23:02.140 --> 00:23:03.473
You've never done it.

282
00:23:03.473 --> 00:23:05.040
Shouldn't we call someone?

283
00:23:05.040 --> 00:23:07.200
It's our house.
We can't call people all the time.

284
00:23:07.200 --> 00:23:09.226
I'll take care of it.

285
00:23:11.060 --> 00:23:12.459
- Do you want help?
- No, it's okay.

286
00:23:12.459 --> 00:23:13.844
It's dangerous, get off.

287
00:23:13.844 --> 00:23:15.227
Get off.

288
00:23:15.227 --> 00:23:16.983
It's dangerous.

289
00:23:19.095 --> 00:23:21.506
Are you still angry?

290
00:23:21.506 --> 00:23:23.780
Who says I'm angry?

291
00:23:23.780 --> 00:23:25.473
Just get off.

292
00:23:28.026 --> 00:23:29.486
OK.

293
00:23:32.910 --> 00:23:34.975
Who do you take me for?

294
00:23:34.975 --> 00:23:37.353
I'll fix it perfectly.

295
00:23:37.353 --> 00:23:39.299
This is nothing.

296
00:23:41.853 --> 00:23:43.699
How strong.

297
00:23:46.100 --> 00:23:47.812
This is easy.

298
00:23:49.145 --> 00:23:51.000
Gosh, it hurts!

299
00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:52.131
- Are you OK?
- Wait.

300
00:23:52.131 --> 00:23:54.331
Ja Yeong, help me! I shot myself.

301
00:23:54.331 --> 00:23:55.946
It hurts me.

302
00:23:56.873 --> 00:23:59.160
- God!
- No, what do we do?

303
00:23:59.160 --> 00:24:01.018
No, don't go up.

304
00:24:01.018 --> 00:24:03.324
Come down, I'll take care of it.

305
00:24:03.324 --> 00:24:05.350
Don't throw!

306
00:24:10.809 --> 00:24:12.675
Hey, don't touch!

307
00:24:20.578 --> 00:24:22.576
Did you just laugh?

308
00:24:24.018 --> 00:24:25.784
I'm sorry,

309
00:24:27.005 --> 00:24:30.085
you look very...

310
00:24:30.835 --> 00:24:32.965
I can't with this.

311
00:24:36.936 --> 00:24:39.079
Health!

312
00:24:42.875 --> 00:24:44.260
Do you feel lighter now?

313
00:24:44.260 --> 00:24:45.980
You did very well.

314
00:24:45.980 --> 00:24:48.600
I wanted to treat you to something better.

315
00:24:48.600 --> 00:24:50.781
Every time I write late at night,

316
00:24:50.781 --> 00:24:54.360
I'm craving a seafood pancake.

317
00:24:54.360 --> 00:24:57.280
I tell myself I'll eat it the next day.
and then I forget.

318
00:24:57.280 --> 00:24:59.880
And every night, I think about it again.

319
00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:02.660
You look very happy.

320
00:25:02.660 --> 00:25:05.065
There seems to be good news.

321
00:25:05.065 --> 00:25:07.186
Is it so obvious?

322
00:25:07.680 --> 00:25:09.980
I don't want to be conceited.

323
00:25:09.980 --> 00:25:13.191
My boyfriend is not a teacher,

324
00:25:13.191 --> 00:25:16.033
but it seems that soon he will teach
in a university.

325
00:25:17.246 --> 00:25:19.880
Double good news!

326
00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:22.693
I thought you already found out.

327
00:25:22.693 --> 00:25:24.320
About what?

328
00:25:31.665 --> 00:25:32.898
Very good.

329
00:25:32.898 --> 00:25:34.760
I chose the materials
for the sophomore class.

330
00:25:34.760 --> 00:25:36.300
I'm still organizing the third year.

331
00:25:36.300 --> 00:25:38.058
Thank you.

332
00:25:40.093 --> 00:25:41.700
I found out from Professor Choi.

333
00:25:41.700 --> 00:25:43.828
Congratulations.

334
00:25:43.828 --> 00:25:45.828
It's thanks to you.

335
00:25:46.513 --> 00:25:48.274
Thank you.

336
00:25:48.274 --> 00:25:52.747
The semester is almost over,
so do it hard.

337
00:25:53.720 --> 00:25:56.576
- OK.
- Yes, finish everything and go.

338
00:25:58.020 --> 00:26:01.651
If you need anything while you prepare for classes

339
00:26:01.651 --> 00:26:04.513
or have questions, come see me whenever you want.

340
00:26:06.461 --> 00:26:08.500
Teacher.

341
00:26:08.500 --> 00:26:09.814
Yeah?

342
00:26:11.250 --> 00:26:12.695
Well...

343
00:26:13.240 --> 00:26:15.399
Be brief, I have a class soon.

344
00:26:16.520 --> 00:26:18.000
No, it's nothing.

345
00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:20.454
I will do my best until the end.

346
00:26:20.454 --> 00:26:22.593
- Great, go ahead!
- Yes.

347
00:26:34.233 --> 00:26:35.680
Hello, it's me.

348
00:26:35.680 --> 00:26:37.300
I have a quick question.

349
00:26:37.300 --> 00:26:39.140
<i>Sure, go ahead.</i>

350
00:26:39.140 --> 00:26:42.886
Nowadays, if you want to be attached,

351
00:26:42.886 --> 00:26:47.246
Do you still have to pay the supervising teacher?

352
00:26:48.512 --> 00:26:50.740
That? That doesn't happen anymore.

353
00:26:50.740 --> 00:26:52.746
Because?

354
00:26:52.746 --> 00:26:54.540
It wasn't Professor Song, right?

355
00:26:54.540 --> 00:26:56.940
No, someone just asked me.

356
00:26:56.940 --> 00:26:58.260
Thanks,

357
00:26:58.260 --> 00:27:00.213
I'll call you later.

358
00:27:00.213 --> 00:27:01.653
Yeah.

359
00:27:16.636 --> 00:27:17.995
Hello.

360
00:27:17.995 --> 00:27:20.031
Jun Seo!

361
00:27:20.685 --> 00:27:22.030
- Get up, come on.
- Because?

362
00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:23.194
Get up, give me your hand.

363
00:27:23.194 --> 00:27:24.536
Because?

364
00:27:30.966 --> 00:27:32.317
What's happening?

365
00:27:32.317 --> 00:27:34.910
Our mouthy writer says...

366
00:27:34.910 --> 00:27:36.623
- Yes?
- that I...

367
00:27:38.504 --> 00:27:40.399
I won the grand prize!

368
00:27:40.399 --> 00:27:41.805
Oh really?

369
00:27:44.083 --> 00:27:47.747
In the publisher's contest,

370
00:27:47.747 --> 00:27:50.180
I won first prize!

371
00:27:51.609 --> 00:27:53.536
- I can't believe it!
- You deserve it.

372
00:27:53.536 --> 00:27:55.982
- Well done.
- I'm very happy!

373
00:27:59.183 --> 00:28:01.430
Did you pack your toothbrush and towel?

374
00:28:01.430 --> 00:28:03.610
Yes, I packed everything.

375
00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:08.538
You said you wanted to go camping.
Just in time.

376
00:28:08.538 --> 00:28:09.670
Yes.

377
00:28:09.670 --> 00:28:13.470
Jun Seo and Hye On are very funny.

378
00:28:17.973 --> 00:28:20.372
What are you going to do, mom?

379
00:28:20.951 --> 00:28:23.198
You will be alone at home.

380
00:28:23.198 --> 00:28:25.447
I have a lot to do.

381
00:28:25.447 --> 00:28:27.550
I'll see my friends and have fun.

382
00:28:27.550 --> 00:28:29.447
Mother.

383
00:28:29.447 --> 00:28:30.747
Even so,

384
00:28:31.553 --> 00:28:33.526
don't forget

385
00:28:34.286 --> 00:28:35.606
feed Oscar.

386
00:28:35.606 --> 00:28:38.273
Do you think I would forget to feed Oscar?

387
00:28:38.853 --> 00:28:40.590
No, it's just that,

388
00:28:40.590 --> 00:28:42.018
in fact, once,

389
00:28:42.018 --> 00:28:44.271
I skipped his meal on purpose...

390
00:28:46.557 --> 00:28:48.284
because I didn't like it

391
00:28:49.491 --> 00:28:51.131
Jun Kyung.

392
00:28:54.956 --> 00:28:56.756
I think dad arrived.

393
00:28:57.496 --> 00:28:59.849
- Leave.
- Have fun.

394
00:29:06.048 --> 00:29:08.046
You are washing my face

395
00:29:08.046 --> 00:29:09.705
and the hair.

396
00:29:09.705 --> 00:29:12.165
You're spoiling me.

397
00:29:12.685 --> 00:29:15.495
Getting hurt has its benefits.

398
00:29:15.495 --> 00:29:18.280
Maybe I should hurt my right hand
next time.

399
00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:20.526
Then you would feed me too, right?

400
00:29:20.526 --> 00:29:22.725
Can you stop talking?

401
00:29:22.725 --> 00:29:25.091
They will arrive at any moment.

402
00:29:26.172 --> 00:29:27.965
Okay, rinsing.

403
00:29:27.965 --> 00:29:29.818
It feels good, doesn't it?

404
00:29:36.946 --> 00:29:39.480
- Dad!
- Thank you for coming here.

405
00:29:42.186 --> 00:29:44.240
- Hello.
- Hello.

406
00:29:45.406 --> 00:29:47.272
Wow, you've grown a lot.

407
00:29:52.166 --> 00:29:53.879
Catch him, catch him.

408
00:29:55.453 --> 00:29:57.060
Did you catch one?

409
00:29:57.060 --> 00:29:58.339
Jun Kyung!

410
00:29:58.339 --> 00:29:59.799
Look at this.

411
00:30:01.204 --> 00:30:03.651
There are many fish,
but he can't catch any.

412
00:30:03.651 --> 00:30:06.032
How can you fail with so many?

413
00:30:06.032 --> 00:30:08.152
Seriously, why can't you catch one?

414
00:30:17.644 --> 00:30:19.517
The more I see Do Hyun...

415
00:30:20.764 --> 00:30:24.123
But I think he's a very good guy.

416
00:30:26.524 --> 00:30:28.663
Do you think so too?

417
00:30:29.311 --> 00:30:30.770
Yes.

418
00:30:30.770 --> 00:30:33.583
They look very good together.

419
00:30:40.376 --> 00:30:42.222
So why do you hesitate?

420
00:30:45.662 --> 00:30:46.971
Jun Kyung.

421
00:30:49.084 --> 00:30:52.383
Not everything was difficult for me.

422
00:30:54.872 --> 00:30:58.339
Maybe you don't know it yet.

423
00:30:58.339 --> 00:31:00.232
That's why

424
00:31:00.232 --> 00:31:02.011
you are afraid,

425
00:31:03.105 --> 00:31:05.444
but someday you will understand.

426
00:31:06.772 --> 00:31:10.019
Love is not just being happy

427
00:31:10.019 --> 00:31:12.545
and have fun together.

428
00:31:19.135 --> 00:31:21.715
Sometimes it's feeling tenderness...

429
00:31:24.753 --> 00:31:26.699
worry.

430
00:31:28.087 --> 00:31:30.693
That is also love.

431
00:31:34.977 --> 00:31:37.323
I was happy...

432
00:31:39.275 --> 00:31:41.341
and I was grateful for everything.

433
00:31:50.223 --> 00:31:52.303
I'm sorry you saw the part of me...

434
00:31:54.610 --> 00:31:56.749
who wanted to let go...

435
00:31:59.515 --> 00:32:02.061
that I wanted to escape.

436
00:32:08.899 --> 00:32:10.199
Jun Kyung,

437
00:32:10.996 --> 00:32:12.896
don't be afraid.

438
00:32:14.410 --> 00:32:16.463
You are much stronger

439
00:32:16.463 --> 00:32:18.996
that me

440
00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:34.059
I caught one!

441
00:32:35.561 --> 00:32:37.655
I have it! Good!

442
00:32:37.655 --> 00:32:39.248
Jun Kyung!

443
00:32:40.094 --> 00:32:42.387
- Look at this.
- We caught a lot!

444
00:33:14.289 --> 00:33:15.589
<i>Okay.</i>

445
00:33:16.696 --> 00:33:19.702
<i>Let's find hope
that anxiety tried to hide.</i>

446
00:33:21.183 --> 00:33:24.009
<i>Even if it doesn't turn out as I imagine,</i>

447
00:33:24.796 --> 00:33:27.089
<i>I won't be disappointed.</i>

448
00:33:28.669 --> 00:33:30.922
<i>I chose to trust myself.</i>

449
00:33:32.909 --> 00:33:35.242
<i>And as soon as I decided that...</i>

450
00:33:36.430 --> 00:33:38.524
<i>I realized.</i>

451
00:33:41.916 --> 00:33:43.495
<i>Of what...</i>

452
00:33:44.697 --> 00:33:46.636
<i>were you so afraid?</i>

453
00:33:52.317 --> 00:33:54.728
- Did you eat two peppers?
- Be careful, it's spicy.

454
00:33:54.728 --> 00:33:56.150
Did you eat it?

455
00:33:56.150 --> 00:33:58.749
My God.

456
00:34:01.623 --> 00:34:04.009
I have something to say.

457
00:34:07.529 --> 00:34:09.577
I'm going to get married

458
00:34:09.577 --> 00:34:11.176
with Do Hyun.

459
00:34:38.436 --> 00:34:40.346
If you were going to say yes anyway,

460
00:34:40.346 --> 00:34:42.512
Why didn't you do it from the beginning?

461
00:34:43.696 --> 00:34:45.416
you know how difficult

462
00:34:45.416 --> 00:34:47.353
which was for me.

463
00:34:47.353 --> 00:34:50.753
Back then, those feelings were real.

464
00:34:55.231 --> 00:34:57.678
And what happened...

465
00:34:59.128 --> 00:35:01.708
with those feelings?

466
00:35:05.116 --> 00:35:06.789
Well, greed?

467
00:35:06.789 --> 00:35:11.093
That diamond ring caught my attention.

468
00:35:22.268 --> 00:35:23.879
No matter how much you think about it,

469
00:35:23.879 --> 00:35:26.545
there is not a single reason

470
00:35:26.545 --> 00:35:28.805
so as not to marry you.

471
00:35:39.748 --> 00:35:41.428
Ju Do Hyun...

472
00:35:44.048 --> 00:35:46.348
would you marry me?

473
00:35:54.258 --> 00:35:55.665
Wait.

474
00:35:57.938 --> 00:36:00.924
Are you proposing to me?

475
00:36:02.739 --> 00:36:04.192
Yes.

476
00:36:09.992 --> 00:36:11.292
Yes.

477
00:36:13.293 --> 00:36:15.126
I want to marry you...

478
00:36:17.406 --> 00:36:18.892
Jun Kyung.

479
00:36:29.412 --> 00:36:31.572
I miss those days.

480
00:36:32.086 --> 00:36:35.612
After a performance,
You walked me to the door.

481
00:36:36.492 --> 00:36:38.798
<i>That is the job of a representative.</i>

482
00:36:39.599 --> 00:36:40.816
<i>So what is it like?</i>

483
00:36:40.816 --> 00:36:44.259
<i>You had a reason to go to Korea. How's that going?</i>

484
00:36:44.259 --> 00:36:46.559
It's not easy.

485
00:36:46.559 --> 00:36:47.976
<i>Why?</i>

486
00:36:47.976 --> 00:36:50.129
<i>Wasn't that something you wanted very much?</i>

487
00:36:50.129 --> 00:36:52.429
Maybe someone else wants it too.

488
00:36:53.532 --> 00:36:54.889
<i>Yun Ju,</i>

489
00:36:54.889 --> 00:36:57.755
<i>you said you couldn't breathe here.</i>

490
00:36:58.666 --> 00:37:00.966
<i>You left to survive.</i>

491
00:37:02.379 --> 00:37:03.723
<i>What are you doing?</i>

492
00:37:03.723 --> 00:37:06.109
<i>It's your birthday, and you're drinking alone?</i>

493
00:37:08.852 --> 00:37:11.032
I miss you, Anna.

494
00:37:11.639 --> 00:37:13.909
<i>You can come back whenever you want.</i>

495
00:37:13.909 --> 00:37:17.522
<i>You also have family here.</i>

496
00:37:18.187 --> 00:37:19.580
<i>Yo.</i>

497
00:37:20.614 --> 00:37:22.600
Thanks, Anna.

498
00:37:37.366 --> 00:37:38.666
Daniel...

499
00:37:42.406 --> 00:37:44.019
what did you think?

500
00:37:47.006 --> 00:37:48.473
It was fun.

501
00:37:48.973 --> 00:37:50.273
No,

502
00:37:51.293 --> 00:37:53.046
not that.

503
00:37:55.126 --> 00:37:56.519
that I

504
00:37:57.833 --> 00:37:59.853
me case

505
00:38:00.366 --> 00:38:01.999
con Jun Kyung.

506
00:38:10.806 --> 00:38:12.392
Bueno,

507
00:38:13.373 --> 00:38:15.433
I think I agree.

508
00:38:23.186 --> 00:38:25.486
Mom will be fine too.

509
00:38:38.918 --> 00:38:40.651
Should we...

510
00:38:45.242 --> 00:38:48.055
hide it from him for now?

511
00:38:51.629 --> 00:38:52.929
Yeah.

512
00:38:54.149 --> 00:38:55.582
GOOD.

513
00:38:56.882 --> 00:38:58.435
About that...

514
00:38:59.742 --> 00:39:01.635
I'll tell you myself.

515
00:39:12.395 --> 00:39:14.339
Congratulations,

516
00:39:14.339 --> 00:39:15.688
dad.

517
00:39:17.889 --> 00:39:20.488
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

518
00:39:31.151 --> 00:39:33.711
Thank you for taking care of Jun Seo.

519
00:39:37.432 --> 00:39:39.279
Are you okay?

520
00:39:39.279 --> 00:39:42.516
They could sleep in the bed.

521
00:39:42.516 --> 00:39:45.523
I love it, I'll sleep here.

522
00:39:45.523 --> 00:39:49.616
Well, then, I'll sleep with you.

523
00:39:50.303 --> 00:39:54.936
It seems like a trip with my best friends.

524
00:39:54.936 --> 00:39:56.387
Yeah.

525
00:39:56.387 --> 00:39:58.307
Tonight seems like one of those nights

526
00:39:58.307 --> 00:40:01.270
that we will remember for a long time.

527
00:40:01.270 --> 00:40:03.889
I hate to see it end like this.

528
00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:06.148
So,

529
00:40:06.148 --> 00:40:08.560
Let's not finish it.

530
00:40:08.560 --> 00:40:09.953
Yeah?

531
00:40:11.493 --> 00:40:14.420
So how about

532
00:40:14.420 --> 00:40:16.225
one more beer each?

533
00:40:16.225 --> 00:40:18.418
- I'm in.
- I'm coming.

534
00:40:18.418 --> 00:40:20.484
Well, I'll go get them!

535
00:40:38.367 --> 00:40:40.147
Dad, are you still awake?

536
00:40:41.954 --> 00:40:43.884
I can't sleep.

537
00:40:43.884 --> 00:40:45.347
¿You?

538
00:40:45.827 --> 00:40:47.487
Me neither.

539
00:40:53.817 --> 00:40:55.360
Why are you awake?

540
00:40:55.360 --> 00:40:58.014
Looks like we won't be sleeping anytime soon.

541
00:40:58.014 --> 00:41:00.047
We entertained ourselves by talking.

542
00:41:04.008 --> 00:41:05.865
Weren't you going to take them?

543
00:41:05.865 --> 00:41:07.654
There is more.

544
00:41:12.361 --> 00:41:14.927
- Health.
- Health.

545
00:41:20.107 --> 00:41:21.928
Congratulations.

546
00:41:21.928 --> 00:41:24.105
I heard you're teaching next semester.

547
00:41:24.105 --> 00:41:26.281
Hye On couldn't stop bragging.

548
00:41:27.288 --> 00:41:28.588
Yeah...

549
00:41:30.138 --> 00:41:31.671
gracias.

550
00:41:34.085 --> 00:41:36.385
You look more adult.

551
00:41:37.751 --> 00:41:40.176
I thought you would make fun of Do Hyun,

552
00:41:40.176 --> 00:41:42.292
saying he would regret it
to marry me or something.

553
00:41:42.292 --> 00:41:44.338
Am I a child or what?

554
00:41:47.262 --> 00:41:48.941
Before,

555
00:41:49.515 --> 00:41:51.821
I worried about things like this.

556
00:41:53.701 --> 00:41:55.332
Jun Kyung

557
00:41:55.332 --> 00:41:58.081
She was beautiful, intelligent and had everything,

558
00:41:59.369 --> 00:42:02.492
but I was worried that
I wouldn't have met the right person.

559
00:42:02.492 --> 00:42:04.229
And as for Jun Seo,

560
00:42:04.229 --> 00:42:06.891
He was handsome and kind,

561
00:42:08.035 --> 00:42:11.355
but I was worried that I hadn't found
what he really loved to do.

562
00:42:13.439 --> 00:42:14.882
It turns out

563
00:42:14.882 --> 00:42:17.611
that everything was a useless worry.

564
00:42:18.425 --> 00:42:20.529
Congratulations, my daughter.

565
00:42:20.529 --> 00:42:21.589
Thank you.

566
00:42:21.589 --> 00:42:24.492
Jun Seo, keep giving it your all.

567
00:42:24.492 --> 00:42:26.031
OK.

568
00:42:30.912 --> 00:42:33.572
I am very grateful to both of them.

569
00:42:35.312 --> 00:42:37.612
I didn't do much for you.

570
00:42:42.845 --> 00:42:44.671
On a night like this,

571
00:42:45.524 --> 00:42:48.805
I wish his mom was here with us.

572
00:43:01.287 --> 00:43:03.124
<i>Please check your account and balance</i>

573
00:43:03.124 --> 00:43:05.149
<i>and select a transaction.</i>

574
00:43:05.149 --> 00:43:06.979
[Balance: 260,000 won]

575
00:43:14.921 --> 00:43:16.992
<i>Remove your card.</i>

576
00:43:16.992 --> 00:43:18.035
[24 hour ATM]

577
00:43:18.035 --> 00:43:20.821
<i>Make sure you have all your belongings.</i>

578
00:43:21.289 --> 00:43:23.750
<i>Thank you for using our service.</i>

579
00:43:27.068 --> 00:43:30.234
[Cash Advance Withdrawal]

580
00:43:50.858 --> 00:43:53.460
[Withdrawal amount: 5,000,000 won]

581
00:44:05.516 --> 00:44:09.239
[Department of Media Studies,
Professor Choi Sung Min]

582
00:44:32.410 --> 00:44:35.210
We came here a lot when Jun Seo was little.

583
00:44:35.210 --> 00:44:36.547
The soup here is amazing.

584
00:44:36.547 --> 00:44:37.716
Oh really?

585
00:44:37.716 --> 00:44:39.542
Let's sit here.

586
00:44:41.656 --> 00:44:43.253
Jun Kyung?

587
00:44:43.253 --> 00:44:45.472
Chang Sik? So long!

588
00:44:45.472 --> 00:44:47.272
- How have you been?
- Yes...

589
00:44:49.923 --> 00:44:51.400
Who is he?

590
00:44:51.400 --> 00:44:52.949
It's...

591
00:44:52.949 --> 00:44:54.950
my boyfriend,

592
00:44:54.950 --> 00:44:56.816
we are going to get married.

593
00:44:58.883 --> 00:45:00.429
Hello.

594
00:45:06.757 --> 00:45:09.403
Did Jun Kyung ever tell you about me?

595
00:45:12.637 --> 00:45:16.110
He said he had a partner
who became a priest.

596
00:45:17.868 --> 00:45:20.494
Just "a companion"?

597
00:45:22.481 --> 00:45:23.960
Yes.

598
00:45:25.795 --> 00:45:27.921
I guess...

599
00:45:27.921 --> 00:45:29.255
who loves you very much, Do Jun.

600
00:45:29.255 --> 00:45:31.961
I'm Do Hyun. Ju Do Hyun.

601
00:45:31.961 --> 00:45:34.148
I'm sorry.

602
00:45:34.148 --> 00:45:36.265
He seems to love you very much,

603
00:45:36.265 --> 00:45:37.801
Do Hyun.

604
00:45:38.428 --> 00:45:41.401
He just called me an ex-colleague.

605
00:45:48.038 --> 00:45:49.524
Because, of course,

606
00:45:50.198 --> 00:45:52.931
Maybe you don't need to know everything.

607
00:45:55.724 --> 00:45:57.944
Yes, it's better.

608
00:45:58.611 --> 00:46:00.871
It's better not to know too much.

609
00:46:02.357 --> 00:46:04.470
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

610
00:46:04.470 --> 00:46:06.018
Thank you.

611
00:46:06.018 --> 00:46:08.201
I won't let another priest officiate the wedding.

612
00:46:08.201 --> 00:46:09.716
What are you taking about?

613
00:46:09.716 --> 00:46:11.434
Your wedding will be in our church, yes or yes.

614
00:46:11.434 --> 00:46:12.935
That's great for me.

615
00:46:12.935 --> 00:46:15.515
You know, it's hard to book places nowadays.

616
00:46:16.074 --> 00:46:18.684
- Hello.
-Won Young?

617
00:46:18.684 --> 00:46:20.577
I just moved to this neighborhood.

618
00:46:20.577 --> 00:46:22.477
Oh really? Excellent.

619
00:46:24.421 --> 00:46:27.092
He is the priest of the local church.

620
00:46:27.092 --> 00:46:28.791
He is my former classmate.

621
00:46:28.791 --> 00:46:30.539
And he is my boyfriend.

622
00:46:31.144 --> 00:46:32.667
Nice to meet you.

623
00:46:32.667 --> 00:46:34.617
Nice to meet you.

624
00:46:35.376 --> 00:46:36.676
But...

625
00:46:37.601 --> 00:46:40.127
You look very familiar to me.

626
00:46:40.962 --> 00:46:42.262
Yes.

627
00:46:42.887 --> 00:46:45.365
I also feel like I've seen you before.

628
00:46:45.365 --> 00:46:48.013
- In a minimarket...
- Do you have a criminal record?

629
00:47:22.492 --> 00:47:23.931
I don't even know if that pork chop

630
00:47:23.931 --> 00:47:26.577
It got into my mouth or nose.

631
00:47:30.077 --> 00:47:32.716
If I screw up even a little here,

632
00:47:32.716 --> 00:47:34.660
I will be in serious trouble.

633
00:47:34.660 --> 00:47:36.893
Are you just realizing it?

634
00:47:40.917 --> 00:47:43.490
I don't know if I should get married like this.

635
00:47:44.591 --> 00:47:46.497
So, cancel it.

636
00:47:50.444 --> 00:47:52.108
Hey, I can't do that.

637
00:47:52.108 --> 00:47:55.050
Our future is there.

638
00:47:55.050 --> 00:47:56.691
You are funny.

639
00:47:58.218 --> 00:48:00.875
So for our second,

640
00:48:00.875 --> 00:48:03.734
Do you want a boy or a girl?

641
00:48:03.734 --> 00:48:05.481
What is this, out of nowhere?

642
00:48:05.481 --> 00:48:07.021
I prefer the second one to be a girl,

643
00:48:07.021 --> 00:48:08.420
and then a child.

644
00:48:10.428 --> 00:48:12.071
Who decided that there is a "later"?

645
00:48:12.071 --> 00:48:14.337
We agree on at least one thing.

646
00:48:14.337 --> 00:48:16.611
The second is a girl.

647
00:48:17.571 --> 00:48:18.997
Who agrees?

648
00:48:19.558 --> 00:48:21.651
I? No no.

649
00:48:23.745 --> 00:48:25.561
Jin Ho,

650
00:48:25.561 --> 00:48:27.585
Are you almost done?

651
00:48:27.585 --> 00:48:28.931
One second,

652
00:48:28.931 --> 00:48:30.808
I'm almost there.

653
00:48:30.808 --> 00:48:32.268
This feels very uncomfortable.

654
00:48:32.268 --> 00:48:35.100
Come out now. I'll tell you how you look.

655
00:48:36.521 --> 00:48:38.054
It's strange, isn't it?

656
00:48:41.328 --> 00:48:43.154
Yes, it's weird.

657
00:48:44.353 --> 00:48:45.754
Good.

658
00:48:48.841 --> 00:48:50.754
Is something wrong?

659
00:48:51.301 --> 00:48:53.461
Come on, hurry up, I feel uncomfortable.

660
00:48:55.301 --> 00:48:57.567
I feel very uncomfortable, hurry up.

661
00:48:58.961 --> 00:49:00.960
Well, wait.

662
00:49:01.832 --> 00:49:03.613
I'm coming.

663
00:49:52.421 --> 00:49:53.938
<i>Simple happiness</i>

664
00:49:53.938 --> 00:49:56.238
<i>sometimes it fills us...</i>

665
00:49:58.581 --> 00:50:01.154
<i>before we know it.</i>

666
00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:04.048
Surprise.

667
00:50:04.048 --> 00:50:07.994
<i>Live as always, each one in his place,</i>

668
00:50:07.994 --> 00:50:10.094
<i>it was enough...</i>

669
00:50:12.201 --> 00:50:14.381
<i>to feel complete.</i>

670
00:50:21.987 --> 00:50:24.534
<i>I didn't expect,</i>

671
00:50:25.801 --> 00:50:28.347
<i>I didn't even have hope for anything else.</i>

672
00:50:30.194 --> 00:50:31.954
<i>But life</i>

673
00:50:32.500 --> 00:50:34.814
<i>has a way of putting</i>

674
00:50:36.074 --> 00:50:38.854
<i>the most unexpected moments in front of us.</i>

675
00:50:41.728 --> 00:50:44.620
My period was late,
so I thought maybe...

676
00:50:50.668 --> 00:50:52.587
Are you disappointed?

677
00:50:53.514 --> 00:50:55.927
I guess I had a little hope...

678
00:50:57.428 --> 00:50:59.914
but now that it is like this,

679
00:51:01.108 --> 00:51:04.120
I'm more worried than disappointed.

680
00:51:06.888 --> 00:51:08.898
There is no rush.

681
00:51:08.898 --> 00:51:12.641
We haven't even had the wedding.

682
00:51:12.641 --> 00:51:14.454
Sincerely,

683
00:51:15.134 --> 00:51:17.204
I haven't tried that hard.

684
00:51:17.204 --> 00:51:18.864
If I really try...

685
00:51:18.864 --> 00:51:20.714
But what if...?

686
00:51:21.548 --> 00:51:22.951
And

687
00:51:22.951 --> 00:51:24.384
if something happens to me?

688
00:51:24.384 --> 00:51:26.944
What could happen to you?

689
00:51:35.256 --> 00:51:37.556
I am an obstetrician and gynecologist.

690
00:51:39.049 --> 00:51:41.469
I am 38 years old

691
00:51:41.469 --> 00:51:43.709
and it would be my first pregnancy.

692
00:51:46.942 --> 00:51:48.646
Should we

693
00:51:48.646 --> 00:51:51.162
have us checked, just in case?

694
00:51:51.162 --> 00:51:53.008
In our hospital? It would be uncomfortable.

695
00:51:53.008 --> 00:51:55.586
So, we'll go somewhere else.

696
00:51:55.586 --> 00:51:58.472
We will go together and they will check us together.

697
00:51:58.472 --> 00:52:01.185
Why you? You don't have any problem.

698
00:52:02.639 --> 00:52:04.918
That's what couples do.

699
00:52:04.918 --> 00:52:07.424
They go together.

700
00:52:45.059 --> 00:52:46.857
It's a mountain road,
so it gets dark fast.

701
00:52:46.857 --> 00:52:48.184
Be careful when coming.

702
00:52:48.184 --> 00:52:49.258
OK.

703
00:52:49.258 --> 00:52:51.443
Thank God.

704
00:53:06.397 --> 00:53:08.087
<i>The number you dialed is not...</i>

705
00:53:08.087 --> 00:53:12.333
What is she so involved in that she can't answer?

706
00:53:39.265 --> 00:53:40.529
Hello.

707
00:53:40.529 --> 00:53:42.032
<i>Where are you?</i>

708
00:53:42.592 --> 00:53:43.949
At university, obviously.

709
00:53:43.949 --> 00:53:45.223
<i>Are you staying late again?</i>

710
00:53:45.223 --> 00:53:48.144
The teacher
He got the research grant, remember?

711
00:53:48.144 --> 00:53:50.705
He asked me to help him until the end.

712
00:53:52.787 --> 00:53:54.011
The teacher is calling me.

713
00:53:54.011 --> 00:53:56.510
I'll be late tonight,
so go to bed first.

714
00:53:56.510 --> 00:53:58.083
Bye bye.

715
00:54:09.310 --> 00:54:12.576
Yes, I am in this square now.

716
00:54:13.403 --> 00:54:14.681
Alright.

717
00:54:14.681 --> 00:54:17.387
- Hey, hurry up.
- Just one more.

718
00:54:17.387 --> 00:54:19.687
One more drink.

719
00:54:20.557 --> 00:54:21.981
- Over there, to the car.
- I have it.

720
00:54:21.981 --> 00:54:23.347
Come on.

721
00:54:25.121 --> 00:54:28.594
<i>The number you dialed is out of service.</i>

722
00:54:49.600 --> 00:54:51.207
Ha Yeong!

723
00:54:51.207 --> 00:54:52.780
Ha Yeong!

724
00:55:06.251 --> 00:55:07.282
Ha Yeong!

725
00:55:07.282 --> 00:55:09.892
Why weren't you answering the phone? I looked for you.

726
00:55:09.892 --> 00:55:11.962
What are you doing here?

727
00:55:21.468 --> 00:55:22.798
Ja Yeong.

728
00:55:22.798 --> 00:55:24.227
Hey.

729
00:55:26.194 --> 00:55:27.661
Are you OK?

730
00:55:29.841 --> 00:55:32.267
I don't know where I am.

731
00:55:37.314 --> 00:55:39.157
suddenly

732
00:55:39.157 --> 00:55:41.457
I don't remember what I was doing here.

733
00:55:42.441 --> 00:55:44.494
I got very scared.

734
00:55:45.268 --> 00:55:47.528
I thought I had to go home.

735
00:55:48.728 --> 00:55:51.574
I had to come back to you...

736
00:55:54.414 --> 00:55:56.714
but I don't know where I am

737
00:55:57.581 --> 00:55:59.841
nor how to get home.

738
00:56:02.594 --> 00:56:04.285
Alright.

739
00:56:04.285 --> 00:56:05.379
I'm sorry,

740
00:56:05.379 --> 00:56:07.488
I arrived late.

741
00:56:07.488 --> 00:56:09.018
It's dark, that's all.

742
00:56:09.018 --> 00:56:11.611
The road is dark,
The trees look the same.

743
00:56:11.611 --> 00:56:14.187
- Anyone would be confused.
- No.

744
00:56:14.954 --> 00:56:16.794
I told you

745
00:56:17.574 --> 00:56:20.045
I loved this forest
after we moved here.

746
00:56:20.045 --> 00:56:22.329
I walked here every day.

747
00:56:22.329 --> 00:56:24.042
How could...?

748
00:56:27.575 --> 00:56:29.875
How could I not know?

749
00:56:42.786 --> 00:56:44.410
Your results look good.

750
00:56:44.410 --> 00:56:46.355
Getting pregnant shouldn't be difficult.

751
00:56:46.355 --> 00:56:48.220
Oh really? What a relief.

752
00:56:48.220 --> 00:56:50.580
See? I told you it would be fine.

753
00:56:50.580 --> 00:56:51.740
but

754
00:56:51.740 --> 00:56:54.238
about his results, Ju Do Hyun...

755
00:56:54.238 --> 00:56:55.587
Yes?

756
00:56:56.230 --> 00:56:58.254
I am afraid that its result

757
00:56:58.254 --> 00:57:00.554
It was negative.

758
00:57:05.670 --> 00:57:07.310
Negative?

759
00:57:08.317 --> 00:57:10.976
What does that mean?

760
00:57:13.130 --> 00:57:15.536
It means infertility.

761
00:57:19.903 --> 00:57:21.160
It just can't be.

762
00:57:21.160 --> 00:57:24.946
Of course, nothing is 100% certain.

763
00:57:25.529 --> 00:57:27.022
We...

764
00:57:30.790 --> 00:57:32.183
I mean,

765
00:57:32.777 --> 00:57:35.357
I already have a son.

766
00:57:38.630 --> 00:57:40.216
Yeah?

767
00:57:42.043 --> 00:57:44.394
Your hormone levels are quite low.

768
00:57:44.394 --> 00:57:46.914
Depending on your FSH levels,

769
00:57:46.914 --> 00:57:49.992
It appears to be non-obstructive azoospermia.

770
00:57:49.992 --> 00:57:54.307
Non-obstructive means it is congenital.

771
00:57:56.841 --> 00:57:58.298
Are you sure?

772
00:57:58.298 --> 00:58:02.194
As I said, there is no absolute security.

773
00:58:03.734 --> 00:58:07.434
A genetic test would be the definitive step.

774
00:58:10.468 --> 00:58:12.264
If it were me,

775
00:58:12.264 --> 00:58:14.980
I would talk to the child's mother.

776
00:58:25.471 --> 00:58:27.304
Do Hyun.

777
00:58:29.877 --> 00:58:31.477
Do Hyun.

778
00:58:39.031 --> 00:58:41.157
I'm going in.

779
00:58:58.839 --> 00:59:00.846
I'm sorry.

780
00:59:00.846 --> 00:59:02.706
I guess I didn't hear you.

781
00:59:18.519 --> 00:59:19.964
I'm sorry. Because of me...

782
00:59:19.964 --> 00:59:21.994
Don't say that.

783
00:59:24.879 --> 00:59:26.325
Daniel

784
00:59:26.912 --> 00:59:28.872
It's my son.

785
00:59:32.012 --> 00:59:34.965
I won't review anything else.

786
00:59:36.092 --> 00:59:38.172
There's no need.

787
00:59:40.166 --> 00:59:43.072
we can act
as if none of this had happened.

788
00:59:45.612 --> 00:59:48.258
nothing happened,

789
00:59:49.106 --> 00:59:51.406
as long as no one knows...

790
00:59:56.951 --> 00:59:58.492
right?

791
00:59:59.992 --> 01:00:01.458
Daniel...

792
01:00:03.652 --> 01:00:05.472
It's my son.

793
01:00:16.157 --> 01:00:17.457
Yes,

794
01:00:18.097 --> 01:00:20.017
Daniel is your son.

795
01:00:22.124 --> 01:00:24.763
Promise me, Jun Kyung.

796
01:00:26.344 --> 01:00:28.070
That no one...

797
01:00:30.263 --> 01:00:32.629
You will find out about today.

798
01:00:38.537 --> 01:00:39.857
Yes.

799
01:00:42.091 --> 01:00:44.391
It will be fine if no one knows.

800
01:01:05.725 --> 01:01:08.846
[Pianist Im Yun Ju]

801
01:01:22.937 --> 01:01:24.691
Im Yun Ju,

802
01:01:24.691 --> 01:01:26.648
I was wondering
What would be your first official move?

803
01:01:26.648 --> 01:01:28.335
back to Korea.

804
01:01:28.335 --> 01:01:30.308
I didn't expect it to be a commercial.

805
01:01:31.902 --> 01:01:34.459
Who was contacted first?

806
01:01:34.459 --> 01:01:36.388
You or Do Hyun?

807
01:01:36.388 --> 01:01:37.559
Does that matter?

808
01:01:37.559 --> 01:01:39.895
We are not strangers.

809
01:01:39.895 --> 01:01:42.146
We are also no strangers to Do Hyun,

810
01:01:42.146 --> 01:01:43.812
but he never asked us for favors like that.

811
01:01:43.812 --> 01:01:46.341
Hey, we're not like her.

812
01:01:50.076 --> 01:01:52.623
But still, are you okay?

813
01:01:53.190 --> 01:01:54.490
About what?

814
01:01:55.790 --> 01:01:57.676
I heard that Do Hyun is getting married.

815
01:02:11.383 --> 01:02:12.659
<i>Who told you that?</i>

816
01:02:12.659 --> 01:02:14.126
<i>Jung Hoon.</i>

817
01:02:14.126 --> 01:02:16.386
<i>I spoke with him a few days ago.</i>

818
01:02:17.889 --> 01:02:19.942
<i>You didn't know?</i>

819
01:02:28.825 --> 01:02:31.057
So you're getting married.

820
01:02:34.644 --> 01:02:37.231
It doesn't seem like you came to congratulate me.

821
01:02:37.231 --> 01:02:39.031
What do you want?

822
01:02:39.971 --> 01:02:42.684
I'm thinking of trying it.

823
01:02:43.904 --> 01:02:45.723
Try what?

824
01:02:46.911 --> 01:02:49.211
I'm moving to this neighborhood.

825
01:02:50.625 --> 01:02:51.376
That?

826
01:02:51.376 --> 01:02:53.009
I already found a place,

827
01:02:53.009 --> 01:02:55.174
I'm moving next month.

828
01:02:55.998 --> 01:02:57.744
Sincerely,

829
01:02:58.324 --> 01:03:00.525
Marriage is not that big a deal.

830
01:03:00.525 --> 01:03:05.325
Know? Do Hyun and I broke up
despite Daniel.

831
01:03:05.325 --> 01:03:07.885
And it hasn't happened yet.

832
01:03:10.178 --> 01:03:11.775
What exactly are you trying to do?

833
01:03:11.775 --> 01:03:14.188
If you were me, what would you do?

834
01:03:15.325 --> 01:03:17.931
If you can't win anyway,

835
01:03:18.418 --> 01:03:20.964
Wouldn't you want to destroy everything?

836
01:03:22.494 --> 01:03:24.184
Do you think feelings are a game?

837
01:03:24.184 --> 01:03:27.520
If Daniel lived closer to his dad,
I would be very happy.

838
01:03:28.358 --> 01:03:30.331
By Daniel,

839
01:03:31.125 --> 01:03:34.391
I would make an even more selfish decision.

840
01:03:34.391 --> 01:03:36.637
You don't even know what Do Hyun thinks.

841
01:03:38.493 --> 01:03:41.997
I would definitely be happy
if your son moved nearby.

842
01:03:56.132 --> 01:03:58.231
I wanted to ask you something.

843
01:04:00.852 --> 01:04:03.605
Is Daniel really Do Hyun's son?

844
01:04:06.811 --> 01:04:08.131
That?

845
01:04:08.805 --> 01:04:12.098
Is Daniel your biological son?

846
01:04:52.692 --> 01:04:54.570
<i>I will only become more famous,</i>

847
01:04:54.570 --> 01:04:55.964
<i>even better.</i>

848
01:04:55.964 --> 01:04:58.011
<i>If that happens, the pressure will be on you.</i>

849
01:04:58.011 --> 01:05:01.598
<i>I have no intention of congratulating you.</i>

850
01:05:01.598 --> 01:05:02.676
<i>You do this</i>

851
01:05:02.676 --> 01:05:04.785
<i>because you want to break up with me, right?</i>

852
01:05:04.785 --> 01:05:07.172
<i>Idiot.</i>

853
01:05:07.172 --> 01:05:08.509
<i>Don't worry,</i>

854
01:05:08.509 --> 01:05:11.812
<i>we just came to make sure
that everything is fine.</i>

855
01:05:12.812 --> 01:05:16.002
<i>I really wanted you to be happy.</i>

856
01:05:16.002 --> 01:05:19.072
<i>I thought I would be happy with you too.</i>

857
01:05:19.072 --> 01:05:21.518
<i>But I don't think I can.</i>

858
01:05:24.252 --> 01:05:26.063
<i>Do you really believe that?</i>

859
01:05:26.063 --> 01:05:28.435
<i>That Daniel might not be your son?</i>

860
01:05:28.435 --> 01:05:30.635
<i>That I like you</i>

861
01:05:30.635 --> 01:05:33.408
<i>is this something I deserve to be punished for?</i>

862
01:05:33.408 --> 01:05:34.919
<i>Why did you do it?</i>

863
01:05:34.919 --> 01:05:36.559
<i>You promised</i>

864
01:05:36.559 --> 01:05:38.485
<i>don't say anything.</i>

865
01:05:38.485 --> 01:05:40.512
<i>I know I was wrong,</i>

866
01:05:40.512 --> 01:05:41.719
<i>but only</i>

867
01:05:41.719 --> 01:05:44.865
<i>I want him to cling to me.</i>

